1) Run a full Bitcoin node (find instructions elsewhere)

2) Run install.py to create a new sqllite3 database
   Can run uninstall.py to drop the database tables and allow rerunning install.py

3) Run import_data.py to import historical price data 
   daily_history.csv must exist in the correct format

4) Run add_blocks.py to save block hashes for reorg detection

5) Run full_node_monitor.py
   This is the main loop
   This will create a pickle.out file to save state and read the database tables created earlier
